item.title: AwokenGodzV2 - 317 Customs Server - new updates - get high!
item.dc:creator: @mrbad23 mrbad23
item.description:
@mrbad23 wrote:

[quote=“Chassy13, post:14, topic:552699”]You can create unique content without creating entirely new models. I dislike models that just flat out look ridiculous, such as duel-wielding godswords, wings, etc… There are some custom models that do look nice, but just don’t go overkill. If you make a new item out of an existing model (renaming it, slight recolor, etc.), add some gameplay around it. Don’t put it in a shop to be bought with coins, actually center an objective around it (this means avoid creating a shop with 20 different colored santa hats, for example).

Your updates are not extremely impressive thus far but take that as constructive feedback. I encourage you to keep going regardless of negativity, it’s the only way you will learn and never be afraid to let your imagination take hold of the server. I can tell that you’re enjoying making new updates so you clearly enjoy the programming.

Good luck.[/quote]
Thank you I really appriecate the feedback and the fact that you dont just come on here saying something like “server sucks” and leaving so thank you

You can create unique content without creating entirely new models. I dislike models that just flat out look ridiculous, such as duel-wielding godswords, wings, etc… There are some custom models that do look nice, but just don’t go overkill. If you make a new item out of an existing model (renaming it, slight recolor, etc.), add some gameplay around it. Don’t put it in a shop to be bought with coins, actually center an objective around it (this means avoid creating a shop with 20 different colored santa hats, for example).

Your updates are not extremely impressive thus far but take that as constructive feedback. I encourage you to keep going regardless of negativity, it’s the only way you will learn and never be afraid to let your imagination take hold of the server. I can tell that you’re enjoying making new updates so you clearly enjoy the programming.

Good luck.
